# Day 1, workshop 2 - claude code hooks

- [x] 1. Create catch-all hook, so each tool last invocation input is stored in separate file. Leave hook output out from git

- [x] 2. Set up fine grained github access token usage.
  - [x] 2a. Accept the Collaborator Invitation

    - Check your email for an invitation to collaborate on 'Plepic-OU/classroomio'
    - Click the link to accept

  - [x] 2b. Create a Fine-Grained Personal Access Token

    1. Go to https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
    2. Set 'Token name' to something descriptive (e.g. `classroomio-workshop`)
    3. Set 'Expiration' to a suitable duration
    4. Under 'Repository access', select 'Only select repositories' and choose `Plepic-OU/classroomio`
    5. Under 'Permissions → Repository permissions', enable 'Read and write' for the following:
      * Contents
      * Issues
      * Pull requests
      * Deployments
      * Discussions
      * Pages
      * Workflows
    6. Click 'Generate token' and copy the token

  - [x] 2c. Store the token in `.devcontainer/github-token` file

- [x] 3. Set up github authentication using the token:
  --- prompt ---
  Add GitHub CLI (gh) authentication to our devcontainer setup:

    1. Add the github-cli devcontainer feature to devcontainer.json
    2. Create .devcontainer/gh-auth.sh that:
     - Reads a token from .devcontainer/github-token
     - Authenticates gh CLI and configures git credentials via gh auth setup-git
     - Prints a helpful message if the token file is missing
     - Runs on every container start (postStartCommand), not just on create
    3. Add .devcontainer/github-token to .gitignore so tokens are never committed
  --- prompt ---

